Soccer, known as football outside North America, is a team sport played by two teams of eleven players on a rectangular field with a goal at each end. The objective is to score by getting the ball into the opposing goal using any part of the body except the hands and arms.

Basketball is a team sport where two teams of five players each try to score points by shooting a ball through the opponent's hoop, which is mounted ten feet high to a backboard at each end of the court. The game is played on a rectangular court and emphasizes dribbling, passing, and shooting.

Tennis is a racket sport that can be played individually against a single opponent or between two teams of two players each. Players use a stringed racket to hit a ball over a net into the opponent's court. The goal is to win points by hitting the ball in such a way that the opponent is unable to return it.

Cricket is a bat-and-ball game played between two teams of eleven players on a circular field. The game centers around batting and bowling, with the batting team aiming to score runs while the bowling and fielding team tries to restrict scoring and dismiss the batsmen.

Baseball is a bat-and-ball game played between two teams of nine players who take turns batting and fielding. The batting team attempts to score runs by hitting a ball thrown by the pitcher and running to a series of four bases arranged in a diamond shape.

Rugby is a contact team sport that originated in England. It is played with an oval-shaped ball that can be carried, kicked, and passed between players. The objective is to score points by touching the ball down in the opponent's in-goal area or kicking it between the goalposts.

Swimming is an individual or team sport that involves moving through water using various strokes, such as freestyle, backstroke, breaststroke, and butterfly. Competitive swimming events range from short sprints to long-distance races in pools or open water.

Golf is a precision club-and-ball sport in which players use various clubs to hit balls into a series of holes on a course in as few strokes as possible. The sport emphasizes skill, strategy, and control.

Volleyball is a team sport where two teams of six players are separated by a net. Each team tries to score points by grounding the ball on the opponent's court, using a combination of passes, sets, and spikes. The game requires coordination, agility, and teamwork.

Boxing is a combat sport in which two people, usually wearing protective gloves, throw punches at each other for a predetermined amount of time in a boxing ring. The objective is to score points by landing punches on the opponent or to knock out the opponent.
